blog.description: i heart Gilmore Girls & Taylor Swift

summary: Oh My My My
title: Oh My My My
body:
For my 1st official TS post I wanna talk about how Mary’s Song should be renamed to Brittany’s song. I don’t see many people talking about it on any platform but can we all agree it is the sweetest song with a real beating heart?

I’ve known my boyfriend since starting high school. We were in the same form group from age 11 to 18 and until a year and a half ago we were just really good friends. We went to uni in the same town, worked at the same school… and, well, the rest is history.

Mary’s/Brittany’s Song speaks to me on approx. 134 levels and all I think about when I hear it is how we’ve essentially grown up together and hope to continue to grow together, reaching 88 and 89.

summary: I wrote this down 2 days after the 1989 show I attended. It's word for word what Taylor said during the Clean speech. I remember...
body:
I wrote this down 2 days after the 1989 show I attended. It’s word for word what Taylor said during the Clean speech. I remember on the night when she spoke those words I felt a relief that someone understood. I was so inspired I wrote it down and put it on my wall. Now when some days just don’t seem to end and I can’t catch a break and feel like I’m the only person struggling, I read this, take a breath, and continue pushing on.

I know you said these words over 3 years ago @taylorswift, but I just want to let you know they are still on my wall and in head and heart when I need them. X
